In contrast, Hodgkin and Nakajima (1972) suggested that sarcoplasmic resistivity, Ri, increased with increasing extracellular osmolarity, possibly owing to an increased myoplasmic viscosity, with reductions in fibre volume in hyperosmotic solutions, reporting a linear increase in Ri with increasing extracellular osmolarity:10\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
